REST APIs (Representational State Transfer APIs):
    • Way for different software systems to communicate over the web using standard HTTP methods.
      They’re one of the most common approaches for building web services
    • REST API follows the principles of Representational State Transfer (REST), an architectural style that uses simple HTTP requests
      to access and manipulate data

Key Concepts:
    • Everything is treated as a resource
    • Each resource is identified by a URL

HTTP Methods:
    • GET       - retrieve data
    • POST      - create new data
    • PUT       - update entire resource
    • PATCH     - update partial resource
    • DELETE    - remove data

🔹 GET (Retrieve data)
    • 200 OK                        - request successful, data returned
    • 304 Not Modified              - cached version is still valid
    • 400 Bad Request               - invalid request format
    • 401 Unauthorized              - authentication required
    • 403 Forbidden                 - access denied
    • 404 Not Found                 - resource doesn’t exist
    • 500 Internal Server Error     - server issue

🔹 POST (Create resource)
    • 201 Created                   - Resource successfully created (most important)
    • 200 OK                        - Sometimes used if returning result without creating new resource
    • 400 Bad Request               - Invalid input data
    • 401 Unauthorized              - Not authenticated
    • 403 Forbidden                 - Not allowed to create
    • 409 Conflict                  - Resource already exists
    • 422 Unprocessable Entity      - Validation errors
    • 500 Internal Server Error     - Server issue

🔹 PUT (Update entire resource)
    • 200 OK                        - Successfully updated
    • 204 No Content                - Updated successfully, no response body
    • 400 Bad Request               - Invalid data
    • 404 Not Found                 - Resource not found
    • 409 Conflict                  - Version conflict
    • 500 Internal Server Error     - Server issue

🔹 PATCH (Partial update)
    • 200 OK                        - Successfully updated
    • 204 No Content                - Updated, no response body
    • 400 Bad Request               - Invalid patch data
    • 404 Not Found                 - Resource not found
    • 422 Unprocessable Entity      - Validation error
    • 500 Internal Server Error     - Server issue

🔹 DELETE (Remove resource)
    • 200 OK                        - Deleted successfully (with response body)
    • 204 No Content                - Deleted successfully (no response body)
    • 400 Bad Request               - Invalid request
    • 401 Unauthorized              - Not authenticated
    • 403 Forbidden                 - Not allowed
    • 404 Not Found                 - Resource not found
    • 500 Internal Server Error     - Server issue


   Method           Success codes             Common Errors
     GET               200,304                    400,401,403,404
     POST              201                        400,401,403,409,422
